<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="100">Marginal base: <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="100">Net amount per unit</strong></p>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="102">Calculation method: <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="102">Whole amount</strong></p>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="104">You buy 8 lamps that cost 25.00 each.</p>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="106">The net amount for the invoice line is 200.00.</p>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="108">The tax is calculated as follows:
Sales tax per unit = 25.00 x 30% = 7.50
Total sales tax = 7.50 x 8 units = 60.00
Total invoice amount = 200.00 + 60.00 = 260.00</p>
<h2 id="net-amount-of-invoice-balance" sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="113">Net amount of invoice balance</h2>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="115">Select this option to determine sales tax rates based on the total value for the invoice, excluding any other taxes.</p>
