<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="127">Marginal base: <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="127">Net amount of invoice balance</strong></p>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="129">Calculation method: <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="129">Interval</strong>
A sales invoice has 2 lines with 4 lamps on each lines for 25.00 each.
The net amount of invoice balance is 4 x 25.00 + 4 x 25.00 = 200.00.
The tax is calculated as follows:
Total sales tax = 50 x 0.30 + 50 x 0.20 + 100 x 0.10 = 15 + 10 + 10 = 35.00
Total invoice amount = 200.00 + 35.00 = 235.00</p>
<h2 id="gross-amount-per-line" sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="136">Gross amount per line</h2>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="138">Select this option to determine sales tax rates based on the value of the line including all other taxes for that line.</p>
<div class="NOTE" sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="140">
<h5>Note</h5>
