<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="189">Marginal base: <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="189">Gross amount per unit</strong>
There is a special duty of 5.00 on each lamp. The duty is added to the net amount before the sales tax calculation.
You buy 8 lamps that cost 25.00 each.
The gross amount per unit is 30.00.
The tax is calculated as follows:
Sales tax per unit = 30 x 30% = 9.00
Total sales tax = 9.00 x 8 = 72.00
Total duty = 5.00 x 8 = 40.00
Total invoice amount = 200.00 + 72.00 + 40.00 = 312.00</p>
<h2 id="invoice-total-incl-other-sales-tax-amounts" sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="199">Invoice total incl. other sales tax amounts</h2>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="201">Select this option to determine sales tax rates based on the total value for the invoice including any other taxes.</p>
<div class="NOTE" sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="202">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="203">In a sales tax group, you can only have one sales tax code with this selection in the Marginal base field</p>
