<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="215">Marginal base: <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="215">Invoice total incl. other sales tax amounts</strong>
Calculation method: <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/marginal-base-field.md" sourcestartlinenumber="216">Interval</strong><br>
There is a special duty of 5.00 on each lamp. The duty is added to the net amount before the sales tax calculation.
You buy 8 lamps that cost 25.00 each. The net amount for the invoice is 200.00.
The gross amount for the invoice is 200.00 + (8 x 5.00) = 240.00.
The tax is calculated as follows:
Total sales tax = 50 x 0.30 + 50 x 0.20 + 140 x 0.10 = 15 + 10 + 14 = 39.00
Total duty = 5.00 x 8 = 40.00
Total invoice amount = 200.00 + 39.00 + 40.00 = 279.00</p>
